## Suggestion

Mention `digest` usage with `Transfer-Encoding` and trailers

 * [ ] use with transfer coding should not affect `digest` because it's not a property of the representation;
 * [ ] use with multiple transfer codings (eg with intermediaries?) should not affect `digest` too;
 * [ ] caveats with transfer codings, trailers and signatures;


## Considerations

- sending `digest` in HTTP trailers may help the sender in dinamically calculating `digest-value`
  while streaming content;
- this only work if it's the Origin-Server to apply the `Transfer-Coding`;
- this may not work for all  `digest-algorithms`, eg. see [mi-sha256 in MICE I-D](https://github.com/martinthomson/http-mice/blob/master/draft-thomson-http-mice.md) for a counter-example); @martinthomson @jyasskin 
- a clarification on using `Digest` with `Transfer-Encoding` should be added before adding this;


